  "market_context": "Analysis focuses on the London session (02:00–05:00 EST) following midnight open. Price forms a consolidation range, then executes a downward displacement (manipulation) back into that range, setting up for expected higher distribution into NY session.",
  "key_observation": "London session showed accumulation (consolidation), then an aggressive downward move that displaced back into the prior range—confirming manipulation phase of the daily AMD cycle.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identify the midnight open and enter London session to observe price behavior within the Asia range.",
    "Step 2: Label the initial sideways price action as 'accumulation' (ACC) during early London hours.",
    "Step 3: Observe an aggressive down-close candle that displaces below the consolidation range but then closes back inside it—this is the manipulation leg.",
    "Step 4: Confirm the manipulation by noting the retest of the consolidation low and subsequent upward momentum toward NY open.",
    "Step 5: Anticipate distribution higher into New York session as the third phase of the daily Power of Three (AMD)."
  ],
  "outcome": null,
  "lessons": "A valid manipulation requires displacement *back into* the accumulation range—not beyond it. Price returning into the range after a sweep signals the manipulation is complete and distribution is imminent in the opposite direction.",
